doc.ContractDescription: THE MASSACHUSETTS SPACE GRANT CONSORTIUM [MASGC) IS AN AFFILIATION OF UNIVERSITIES, FOUR YEAR AND COMMUNITY COLLEGES, AND INFORMAL EDUCATION INSTITUTIONS ACROSS THE STATE. OVER THE PAST DECADE, MASGC HAS BUILT UP ITS MEMBERSHIP TO REFLECT THE DIVERSITY OF EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS IN THE STATE, FROM THE BERKSHIRES TO CAPE COD AND THE ISLANDS, IN KEEPING WITH NASA OFFICE OF EDUCATION ANNUAL PERFORMANCE GOAL OVERRIDING MOTIVATION IS TO USE ITS RESOURCES TO ALLOW MASSACHUSETTS STUDENTS TO PARTICIPATE IN STEM RELATED ACTIVITIES RELEVANT TO NASAS MISSION THAT THEY WOULD NOT BE ABLE TO WITHOUT SPACE GRANT SUPPORT. ITS GOALS AND OBJECTIVES ARE TO CONTRIBUTE TO THE DEVELOPMENT OF EDUCATION, RESEARCH AND TECHNOLOGY IN STEM DISCIPLINES IN ALIGNMENT WITH NASAS STRATEGIC GOALS. THEREFORE, THE CONSORTIUM HAS A THREE FOLD MISSION: HIGHER EDUCATION&RESEARCH THE CONSORTIUM PROVIDES NASA COMPETENCY BUILDING OPPORTUNITIES IN HIGHER EDUCATION AND RESEARCH BY WAY OF RESEARCH FELLOWSHIPS AND SCHOLARSHIPS AT MASGC AFFILIATE INSTITUTIONS, AND INTERNSHIPS AT NASA CENTERS TO THE MAXIMUM NUMBER OF MASSACHUSETTS STUDENTS, REFLECTING THE DIVERSITY OF STUDENTS THROUGHOUT THE STATE, TO CREATE A SKILLED WORKFORCE FOR NASA, THE AEROSPACE INDUSTRY AND ACADEMIA. STEM RETENTION THE CONSORTIUM PROVIDES CONTINUING AND IN SERVICE OPPORTUNITIES TO HELP TEACHERS MAINTAIN OR ACQUIRE COMPETENCY IN STEM AND ACCESS NASA EDUCATIONAL MATERIALS. IT EXTENDS SPACE GRANT PROGRAMS AND OPPORTUNITIES TO THE BROADEST POSSIBLE CROSSSECTION OF THE MASSACHUSETTS POPULATION, PARTICULARLY ENCOURAGING PARTICIPATION BY WOMEN AND MINORITIES. STEM INFORMAL EDUCATION THE CONSORTIUM PROMOTES STEM LITERACY AND AWARENESS OF NASA'S MISSION THROUGH ITS OUTREACH PARTNERS AND ALSO THROUGH PUBLIC EVENTS WITH ASSISTANCE FROM NASA. IN THE FIRST FOUR YEARS OF THE CURRENT 5 YEAR GRANT, MASGC HAS GIVEN OUT 331 FELLOWSHIPS AND INTERNSHIPS TO STUDENTS FROM 18 AFFILIATE INSTITUTIONS. AT LAST YEARS NATIONAL DIRECTORS MEETING, MASGC WAS PUBLICLY CONGRATULATED FOR HAVING THE LARGEST NUMBER OF FELLOWSHIPS OF ANY SPACE GRANT. WE INTEND TO CONTINUE THIS POLICY. MASGC HAS WORKED HARD TO MEET NASAS DIVERSITY GOALS. DURING THE FIRST FOUR YEARS OF THE CURRENT 5 YEAR GRANT, 40 PERCENT OF ALL FELLOWSHIP, INTERNSHIP, HIGHER EDUCATION AND RESEARCH AWARDS WENT TO FEMALES, AND 18 PERCENT WENT TO UNDERREPRESENTED MINORITIES.
